:::summary
Christian history spans two thousand years, from the ministry of Jesus Christ in first-century Judea to the global faith of over 2 billion believers today. It is a story of astonishing growth, fierce persecution, theological controversy, reform movements, and — from a Latter-day Saint perspective — the Great Apostasy and eventual Restoration of the original church. Understanding Christian history helps make sense of why the world needed a restoration.
